ot values. The most likely P-dot value\nfor the pre-ZAHB variables is ~-0.3 d/Myr, but more extreme P-dot values are\nalso possible: 38% of the variables are predicted to have P-dot < -0.8 d/Myr.\nIt appears likely, therefore, that some RRL stars in M3 with high (absolute)\nP-dot values are pre-ZAHB pulsators in disguise. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jul 2008 17:30:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
