 observation. The correlation\nbetween nuclear and disk colours and the small colour gradients hints at an\nintertwined star formation history for bulges and disks: probably, most of our\nred bulges formed in a process in which truncation of star formation in the\nbulge did not destroy the disk.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jul 2008 21:39:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
